<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                van Limburg</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-28"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 28, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 22d instant and of its enclosure, relative
                            to the case of the Netherlands ship Geziena Hildegonda, and to inform
                            you that I have transmitted a translation thereof to the Secretary of
                            the Navy, whose attention has been recalled to the matter.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roest van Limburg.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>